HEADWORD: electronic device
<hw>electronic device</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a device depending on the
principles of electronics and using the manipulation of electron flow
for its operation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Numerous electronic devices are in daily use, among them
the <stype>television</stype>, <stype>radio</stype>,
<stype>computer</stype>, <stype>robot</stype>,
<stype>transmitter</stype>, <stype>receiver</stype>, <stype>VCR</stype>,
<stype>CD player</stype>, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

